wikipedia_page.main: Stanley Charles Sayer (2 February 1895 – 3 April 1982) was an English footballer who scored 51 goals from 201 appearances in the Football League playing for Millwall Athletic, Tranmere Rovers, New Brighton, Wigan Borough, Lincoln City and Southend United. He played as a centre forward or inside forward. He also played non-league football for Ramsgate Town, Northfleet and Dartford.
